 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Research & Development Contractor Verata Health Remote Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Research & Development Contractor 
If you are highly driven and want to learn valuable work skills that are applicable to both health care and technology, we want to hear from you. As a bonus, you will improve your resume and college/professional credentials and earn a recommendation from alumni of Harvard, MIT, Duke, Google, Apple and SpaceX all while helping create something that will help people get the care they need more quickly. 
As an R & D Contractor you will: 
Help create the next level of Artificial Intelligence 
Enhance the application that helps doctors and nurses get patients the care they need as quickly as possible 
Work from home on a Data Entry focused role 
Take important data from an insurance company and enter it into an application 
Have flexible work hours with only a few meetings per week 
The ideal R & D Contractor will have: 
Strong knowledge of Excel Spreadsheets 
25-40+ flexible hours with some business hour availability 
Ability to learn quickly, work independently, and be proactive in asking questions 
Strong organization, attention to detail and follow-up skills 
Opportunities to earn additional responsibility 
Some knowledge of health care and medical terminology a PLUS 
A passion for helping build a company that is building technology that helps patients get the care they need 
Work location and hours: 
This is a work-from-home, data entry focused role. The work hours are flexible with only a few meetings per week which you will need to attend via Zoom. Training, meetings, questions and feedback will be during normal business hours, though you can work when it‚Äôs convenient for you. 
 
